        <title>Application for Administrators</title>
        <contents>&lt;h2 style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #5fa6ca; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;img style="float: right; margin: 15px;" alt="Stick figures standing in elevator" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/stick%20figures%20in%20elevator%20%281%29.png" width="375" height="282" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop an elevator speech&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;In your role, you  interact with teachers, professional development providers, policy makers, and learners. What would you tell them about the need for increasing the rigor of instruction in adult ESL? Draw on examples from the resources (Parrish and Johnson, Alignment &lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/M1U1_S43_Survey%20Results_508.pdf" title="Survey Results"&gt;Survey results&lt;/a&gt;, employment data, CCRS intro) and vignettes presented in the unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Try out your speech with two colleagues&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;What questions did they have and how were you able to respond?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;What seemed to be the most surprising thing to them?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;What do you feel confident talking about with regard to increasing the rigor of instruction in adult ESL and what questions do you still have? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;How can you learn more?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Share your responses to this activity in your Community of Practice, or &lt;a href="https://community.lincs.ed.gov/comment/16536#comment-16536"&gt;share with your colleagues on LINCS here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="yiv6737391600MsoNormal" id="yui_3_16_0_1_1444861047032_44651"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium; color: #666699;"&gt;&lt;span id="yui_3_16_0_1_1444861047032_44650"&gt;You have reached the end of this lesson.  You may review any of the content in this lesson using the &lt;b&gt;Lesson Menu&lt;/b&gt; on the left of the screen&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
