        <title>Application for Instructors</title>
        <contents>&lt;h2 style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #8ebb41;"&gt;&lt;img style="margin: 15px; float: right;" alt="" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Learners%20in%20a%20classroom%20%281%29.png" width="367" height="244" /&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;Pulling it All Together in Your Context&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part I:&lt;/strong&gt; Create a vignette of one learner, interviewing them if possible. Feel free to use the help of an interpreter if needed:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;What is his or her background? What are his or her hopes for the future, at home and with family, in the community, at school or at work?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;Conduct the same analysis for your learner that you did for the vignettes in the unit. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;What can we infer about this learner’s personal and professional goals that she or he may not have been able to articulate?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;What complex language and skills are required if this learner one day wants to achieve his or her goals? How might this learner’s strengths and challenges impact acquisition of the more complex language and skills presented in the unit?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part II:&lt;/strong&gt; With your own learners in mind, describe what academic language, listening, reading, or critical thinking skills would benefit them and describe how you could incorporate practice with at least 2 of those skills in a lesson with that learner. Draw on examples from the &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/M1U1_S37_45_SampLes_508.docx" title="Sample Lesson Enhancements"&gt;Sample Lesson Enhancement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; or &lt;a href="https://lincs.ed.gov/professional-development/resource-collections/profile-418" title="Parrish and Johnson" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Parrish and Johnson&lt;/em&gt; (2010)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;Share your responses to this activity in your Community of Practice, or &lt;a href="https://community.lincs.ed.gov/comment/16536#comment-16536" title="Unit 1 LINCS Discussion"&gt;share with your colleagues on LINCS here.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;Present your vignette, analysis and lesson enhancements to colleagues if you are working in a PLC, study circle or peer/small group.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
