        <title>Influences of the CCRS for Administrators</title>
        <contents>&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;We can’t talk about increasing rigor of instruction in adult ESL without mentioning the &lt;strong&gt;College and Career Readiness Standards&lt;/strong&gt;. These standards serve to raise awareness and understanding of the critical skills and knowledge expected and required for success in colleges, technical training programs, and employment in the 21st century (Pimentel, 2013). The work you are doing in this module complements CCRS implementation that may be going on in your state.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;“The importance of college and career readiness for adult students cannot be overstated. Increasingly, students entering the workforce are discovering that they need critical knowledge and skills that are used on a regular basis. They recognize that pursuing a career pathway that pays enough to support a family and provides genuine potential for advancement hinges on being able to perform the complex tasks identified by the CCRS as critical for postsecondary success. ….It is crucial, then, that adult education programs provide students the opportunity to acquire these skills to pursue their long-term career aspirations and goals.”&lt;/em&gt; (Pimentel, 2013, p. 2).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
