        <title>Key Advances</title>
        <contents>&lt;h2 style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;Key advances prompted by the College and Career Readiness Standards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;These key advances prompted by the College and Career Readiness Standards can serve as foundational principles for our  work in this module:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complexity&lt;/strong&gt;: Regular practice with complex text (and its academic language)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evidence&lt;/strong&gt;: Reading, writing, and speaking grounded in evidence from text&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px; text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge&lt;/strong&gt;: Building knowledge through content-rich nonfiction&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;"&gt;While this module is not focused on the CCRS, it is important that administrators (and teachers) see the connections. This module can give programs a head start with thinking about CCRS implementation in adult ESL.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
